

LISTENER FILEs LOCATION and TOOLs:
---------------------------------
cd $ORACLE_HOME/network/admin/       listener.ora and tnsnames.ora
netmgr  and netca / tools to config oracle net listerner


START/STOP/RELOAD LISTENER:
--------------------------
[oracle@test] lsnrctl start/status/stop/reload   /Start defaul listener
OR 
[oracle@test] lsnrctl      / Start Modified listener
lsnrctl>start L2           / Modified listener 
tnsping tnsname            / To check whether listener is ready

SQL>alter system register;  /FORCE TO START LISTENER BEFORE 1 MINUTE


CREATE(NEW)/EDIT A LISTENER:
---------------------------
STEP:01 (Add line to listener.ora)
L2 = (DESCRIPTION =(ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP)(HOST = test.com)(PORT = 1560)))

STEP:02 (Add line to tnsnames.ora)
L2 =  (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP)(HOST = test.com)(PORT = 1560))

STEP:03 (Login:sqlplus / as sysdba)
SQL> show parameter local
SQL> alter system set local_listener= "LISTENER_ORCL , L2";



 

